text: The 1991–92 Sporting de Gijón season was the 30th season of the club in La Liga, the 16th consecutive after its last promotion. ==Overview== Real Sporting was eliminated in the round of 32 of the UEFA Cup. Previously, it eliminated Partizan after a penalty shoot-out in Istanbul. Joaquín Alonso retired from football at the end of the season, after spending all his career at the club and playing 479 matches at La Liga, establishing a new record.
